      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I can see your point about certain expansions bringing certain benefits. But, even if someone "buys" the expansion, they still dont get the benefit. They have to join a guild. So if I choose not to buy the expansion, then heck no, don't give me the AA's, benefits ect. But if I buy the expansion...?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;As far as guild tribute goes, your right. If you don't own GoD, you don't get it. But....Guild Tribute is not available to the entire guild such as the Guil Hall is. It's activated and deactivated on raids by certain people. Your normal Joe Schmoe from &amp;lt;Guild_01&amp;gt; can't use Guild Tribute at 4am when there are only 3 members on, but he can waltz in to the Guild Hall.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;As far as PoK? Well, thats a zone available to everyone now, even if they don't have the PoP expansion...&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Make expansions, make me work harder to get new and better gear, make me work harder to get new and better AA's...all fine and dandy...&amp;nbsp;but you make me associate myself with a group of people, I got issues. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I bought it anyway. Simply because there were a couple things I wanted. But, you know me...none of my seven alts are tagged and Legion is still Nocturnal. I won't sway on that part. For me joining a guild needs to be more than just use of guild hall. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I still think it's biased. Don't expect a change from Sony&amp;nbsp;or anyone to agree with me, but you got my two copper anyway! My view may change slightly when the server's are merged. Maybe there will be an actual player base again. Maybe I won't have to search for hours to get certain buffs, only to have them waste away looking for group forever. At a time when buff suspension is&amp;nbsp;bliss to all players, only tagged get to use it...&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
